import React from 'react' const UserEmail = ({user}) => { function containsNumbers(str) { return /[0-9]/.test(str); } var car = user.car var email = user.email return (
{ (car === "BMW" || car === "Mercedes-Benz" || car === "Audi") && (!containsNumbers(email)) ? <> {user.id} {user.first_name} {user.last_name} {user.email} {user.gender} {user.income} {user.city} {user.car} {user.quote} {user.phone_price} : <> }
) } export default UserEmail
